'''Jens Petter Hauge''' (born 12 October 1999) is a Norwegian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left winger]] for [[Eliteserien]] club [[FK Bodø/Glimt|Bodø/Glimt]] and the [[Norway national football team|Norway national team]].

==Club career==
===Bodø/Glimt===
Born in [[Bodø (town)|Bodø]], [[Nordland]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.altomfotball.no/element.do?cmd=player&personId=313176&tournamentId=1&seasonId=338&teamId=307&useFullUrl=false |title=Jens Petter Hauge |work=altomfotball.no |publisher=TV2 |access-date=1 May 2016 |archive-date=27 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190327090920/http://www.altomfotball.no/element.do?cmd=player&personId=313176&tournamentId=1&seasonId=338&teamId=307&useFullUrl=false |url-status=dead }}</ref> spending his childhood years in FK Vinkelen, and progressing through the youth academy of [[FK Bodø/Glimt|Bodø/Glimt]], Hauge signed his first professional contract with the club on 12 April 2016.<ref name="an-120416">{{cite web |last1=Høgland |first1=Stian |title="Det er bedre for meg å få være involvert i et A-lag her, enn med et akademilag i England" |url=https://www.an.no/sport/glimt/fotball/det-er-bedre-for-meg-a-fa-vare-involvert-i-et-a-lag-her-enn-med-et-akademilag-i-england/s/5-4-290313 |website=an.no |publisher=Avisa Nordland |access-date=2 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160413113430/https://www.an.no/sport/glimt/fotball/det-er-bedre-for-meg-a-fa-vare-involvert-i-et-a-lag-her-enn-med-et-akademilag-i-england/s/5-4-290313 |archive-date=13 April 2016 |language=no |date=12 April 2016}}</ref> The following day he made his senior debut in a 6–0 [[Norwegian Football Cup|cup]] win against [[IF Fløya]] as a 64th-minute [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Fitim Azemi]]. He immediately scored a [[Hat-trick#Association football|hat-trick]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Høgland |first1=Stian |title=Glimt-debutant med ekte hattrick i cupkampen mot Fløya |url=https://www.an.no/glimt/glimt-debutant-med-ekte-hattrick-i-cupkampen-mot-floya/s/5-4-290872|website=an.no |publisher=Avisa Nordland |access-date=2 October 2020 |language=no |date=13 April 2016 |archive-date=2 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201002084236/https://www.an.no/glimt/glimt-debutant-med-ekte-hattrick-i-cupkampen-mot-floya/s/5-4-290872 |url-status=live}}</ref> Hauge made his league debut on 23 April against [[Strømsgodset Toppfotball|Strømsgodset]], where he came on as a late substitute as Bodø/Glimt lost 2–0.<ref>{{cite web |title=LIVE Strømsgodset IF - FK Bodø/Glimt - Eliteserien - 23 April 2016 |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/tippeligaen/2016/live-stromsgodset-if-fk-bodo-glimt_mtc836450/live.shtml |website=eurosport.com |publisher=Eurosport |access-date=2 October 2020 |archive-date=5 December 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201205172917/https://www.eurosport.com/football/tippeligaen/2016/live-stromsgodset-if-fk-bodo-glimt_mtc836450/live.shtml |url-status=live }}</ref> In the next league games he featured regularly, and on 8 July, he scored his first top-flight goal in the 4–1 away win over [[IK Start]], becoming Bodø/Glimt's youngest ever goalscorer in the [[Eliteserien]].<ref name="glimt-profile">{{cite web |title=Jens Petter Hauge / Bodø/Glimt |url=https://www.glimt.no/lag/jens-petter-hauge |website=glimt.no |publisher=[[FK Bodø/Glimt]] |access-date=2 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180215044353/https://www.glimt.no/lag/jens-petter-hauge |archive-date=15 February 2018 |language=no }}</ref> In the 2016 season, he made 20 league appearances in which he scored one goal,<ref name="SW">{{cite web |title=J. Hauge - Profile |url=https://us.soccerway.com/players/jens-hauge/442667/ |website=us.soccerway.com |publisher=Perform Group |access-date=2 October 2020 |archive-date=7 November 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107224419/http://us.soccerway.com/players/jens-hauge/442667/ |url-status=live}}</ref> as Bodø/Glimt suffered relegation to the second-tier [[Norwegian First Division]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Braastad |first1=Even |last2=Strøm |first2=Ole Kristian |title=Drama da Bodø/Glimt rykket ned |url=https://www.vg.no/sport/fotball/i/ldyXe/drama-da-bodoe-glimt-rykket-ned |website=vg.no |publisher=[[Verdens Gang|VG]] |access-date=2 October 2020 |language=no |date=6 November 2016 |archive-date=29 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201029145424/https://www.vg.no/sport/fotball/i/ldyXe/drama-da-bodoe-glimt-rykket-ned |url-status=live}}</ref>

In the following season, Hauge established himself as an undisputed starter as Bodø/Glimt won the second-tier championship and made their immediate return to the top-flight Eliteserien.<ref>{{cite web |title=Bodø/Glimt tilbake i Eliteserien |url=https://www.dagsavisen.no/sport/bodo-glimt-tilbake-i-eliteserien-1.1033909 |publisher=[[Dagsavisen]] |access-date=2 October 2020 |language=no |date=1 October 2017 |archive-date=29 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201029173633/https://www.dagsavisen.no/sport/bodo-glimt-tilbake-i-eliteserien-1.1033909 |url-status=live}}</ref> He made a significant contribution that season, scoring two goals and making 13 assists.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Nair |first1=Varun |title=Jens Petter Hauge: Everything You Need to Know About the Reported New AC Milan Winger |url=https://lastwordonsports.com/football/2020/10/01/jens-petter-hauge-everything-you-need-to-know-about-the-reported-new-ac-milan-winger/ |publisher=LWOS |access-date=2 October 2020 |date=1 October 2020 |archive-date=27 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201027053843/https://lastwordonsports.com/football/2020/10/01/jens-petter-hauge-everything-you-need-to-know-about-the-reported-new-ac-milan-winger/ |url-status=live}}</ref> At the start of the 2018 season, Hauge again lost his starting role, and as a result, was loaned to the second-tier club [[Aalesunds FK]] on 15 August 2018, halfway through the season, after 11 league appearances in which he scored no goals.<ref name="SW" /> In Aalesund, he had made only six league appearances by the end of the season.<ref name="SW" />

During the course of the following season, Hauge made it back into the starting line-up of Bodø/Glimt. On 10 November 2019, he scored both goals for his club in a 2–3 away defeat to [[Rosenborg BK|Rosenborg]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Zerener |first1=Anders |title=Rosenborg gikk seirende ut i skjebnekampen mot Bodø/Glimt |url=https://www.nettavisen.no/sport/rosenborg-gikk-seirende-ut-i-skjebnekampen-mot-bodoglimt/3423876485.html |website=nettavisen.no |publisher=[[Nettavisen]] |access-date=2 October 2020 |language=no |date=10 November 2019 |archive-date=29 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201029170149/https://www.nettavisen.no/sport/rosenborg-gikk-seirende-ut-i-skjebnekampen-mot-bodoglimt/3423876485.html |url-status=live }}</ref> That season, he made 28 league appearances in which he scored seven goals and registered two assists.<ref name="SW" />

Scheduled to begin in March, the [[2020 Eliteserien|2020 season]] was postponed until June 2020 due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic in Norway|COVID-19 pandemic]]. Hauge and Bodø/Glimt got off to an excellent start.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tóth |first1=Zoltán |title=Eliteserien 2020: FK Bodo/Glimt, the Scandinavian Atalanta – team analysis |url=https://totalfootballanalysis.com/competitions/eliteserien/eliteserien-2020-fk-bodo-glimt-the-scandinavian-atalanta-team-analysis-tactics |publisher=Total Football Analysis |access-date=2 October 2020 |date=16 July 2020 |archive-date=1 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201001182850/https://totalfootballanalysis.com/competitions/eliteserien/eliteserien-2020-fk-bodo-glimt-the-scandinavian-atalanta-team-analysis-tactics |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Kolberg |first1=Sindre |title=Sår tvil om overgangen til Belgia: – Det blir tatt en avgjørelse de neste dagene |url=https://bodonu.no/saar-tvil-om-overgangen-til-belgia-det-blir-tatt-en-avgjorelse-de-neste-dagene/19.07-11:01 |website=bodonu.no |publisher=Bodø Nu |access-date=2 October 2020 |language=no |date=18 July 2020 |archive-date=5 December 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201205172919/https://bodonu.no/saar-tvil-om-overgangen-til-belgia-det-blir-tatt-en-avgjorelse-de-neste-dagene/19.07-11:01 |url-status=live}}</ref> After ten match-days, the club surprisingly took a lead in the league table.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ihle |first1=Marthe |last2=Christiansen |first2=Synne Sofie |title=Blir: - Vil vinne gull med Glimt |url=https://www.dagbladet.no/sport/blir---vil-vinne-gull-med-glimt/72692048 |publisher=Dagbladet |access-date=2 October 2020 |language=no |date=26 July 2020 |archive-date=29 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201029165549/https://www.dagbladet.no/sport/blir---vil-vinne-gull-med-glimt/72692048 |url-status=live}}</ref> At that point, Hauge had already scored six goals and assisted six.<ref name="SW" /> He also managed to impress in the [[2020–21 UEFA Europa League qualifying phase and play-off round|UEFA Europa League qualifiers]]. In the narrow 2–3 away defeat to Italian club [[A.C. Milan]], Hauge was directly involved in both his team's goals.<ref>{{cite web |title=Milan-Bodo Glimt 3-2: gol e highlights. Rossoneri qualificati ai playoff di Europa League |url=https://sport.sky.it/calcio/europa-league/2020/09/24/milan-bodo-glimt-risultato-gol |website=sport.sky.it |publisher=[[Sky Sports]] |access-date=2 October 2020 |language=it |date=24 September 2020 |archive-date=2 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201002034720/https://sport.sky.it/calcio/europa-league/2020/09/24/milan-bodo-glimt-risultato-gol |url-status=live}}</ref> As a result, media reported that the Rossoneri were interested in signing him.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Indsetviken |first1=Emil H. |last2=Frederiksen |first2=Benjamin |title=Italienske medier hevder AC Milan vil kjøpe Jens Petter Hauge fra Bodø/Glimt |url=https://www.nrk.no/nordland/glimt-treneren-tror-ac-milan-ville-passet-jens-petter-hauge-veldig-godt-1.15174905 |website=nrk.no |publisher=NRK |access-date=2 October 2020 |language=no |date=25 September 2020 |archive-date=2 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201002101348/https://www.nrk.no/nordland/glimt-treneren-tror-ac-milan-ville-passet-jens-petter-hauge-veldig-godt-1.15174905 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Kupitz |first1=Jan |title=Norwegen-Talent Hauge zur AC Milan: "Freue mich, mit Zlatan zu spielen" |url=https://www.90min.de/posts/norwegen-talent-hauge-zur-ac-milan-freue-mich-mit-zlatan-zu-spiele |website=90min.de |publisher=90min |access-date=2 October 2020 |language=de |date=29 September 2020 |archive-date=19 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201019233316/https://www.90min.de/posts/norwegen-talent-hauge-zur-ac-milan-freue-mich-mit-zlatan-zu-spiele |url-status=live}}</ref>

===AC Milan===
On 1 October 2020, Hauge signed a five-year contract with [[Serie A]] club A.C. Milan.<ref>{{cite press release|date=1 October 2020|title=Comunicato Ufficiale: Jens Petter Hauge|url=https://www.acmilan.com/it/news/articoli/media/2020-10-01/comunicato-ufficiale-jens-petter-hauge|access-date=1 October 2020|website=[[A.C. Milan]]|language=it|archive-date=1 October 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201001091304/https://www.acmilan.com/it/news/articoli/media/2020-10-01/comunicato-ufficiale-jens-petter-hauge|url-status=live}}</ref> Three days later, he made his debut in a 3&ndash;0 win over [[Spezia Calcio|Spezia]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Manfredi |first1=Jacopo |title=Milan-Spezia 3-0, doppio Leao e Hernandez: i rossoneri restano in vetta |url=https://www.repubblica.it/sport/calcio/serie-a/2020/10/04/news/milan-spezia_3-0_doppio_leao_e_hernandez_i_rossoneri_restano_in_vetta-269470759/ |publisher=[[la Repubblica]] |access-date=9 October 2020 |language=it |date=4 October 2020 |archive-date=9 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201009055009/https://www.repubblica.it/sport/calcio/serie-a/2020/10/04/news/milan-spezia_3-0_doppio_leao_e_hernandez_i_rossoneri_restano_in_vetta-269470759/ |url-status=live}}</ref> On 22 October, he scored his first goal for Milan in a 3–1 win at [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] in the group stage of the [[2020–21 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/54528918|title=Neil Lennon was "encouraged" despite his Celtic side being overcome by Serie A leaders AC Milan in their Europa League group stage opener in Glasgow.|website=BBC|date=22 October 2020|access-date=5 November 2020|archive-date=1 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201101144554/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/54528918|url-status=live}}</ref> On 22 November, he scored his first Serie A goal in a 3–1 away win over [[S.S.C. Napoli|Napoli]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sempremilan.com/player-ratings-napoli-1-3-ac-milan-ibrahimovic-decisive-hauge-opens-account |title=Player Ratings: Napoli 1-3 AC Milan – Ibrahimovic decisive again; Hauge opens league account |website=SempreMilan |date=22 November 2020 |access-date=22 November 2020 |archive-date=22 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201122222038/https://sempremilan.com/player-ratings-napoli-1-3-ac-milan-ibrahimovic-decisive-hauge-opens-account |url-status=live}}</ref>

===Eintracht Frankfurt===
On 10 August 2021, [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] announced that Hauge would join the [[Bundesliga]] club on a season-long loan with an option to make the deal permanent.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Jens Petter Hauge wechselt zur Eintracht|url=https://profis.eintracht.de/news/jens-petter-hauge-wechselt-zur-eintracht-134705/|access-date=2021-08-10|website=Eintracht Frankfurt|language=de}}</ref> He scored a goal in his Frankfurt debut, although in a 5–2 loss against [[Borussia Dortmund]], on 14 August.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/borussia-dortmund-eintracht-frankfurt-live-line-ups-stats-haaland-reyna-16863|title=Erling Haaland orchestrates big Borussia Dortmund win against Eintracht Frankfurt|date=14 Aug 2021|access-date=25 December 2021}}</ref>

On 28 May 2022, Eintracht Frankfurt announced that they had activated the purchase option for Hauge from [[Serie A]] club [[A.C. Milan|AC Milan]] following his one-year loan. Hauge signed his contract until 2026.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Hauge signs permanently |url=https://en.eintracht.de/news/eintracht-verpflichtet-hauge-fest-142109 |access-date=2022-05-28 |website=Eintracht Frankfurt |language=en}}</ref>

====Loan to Gent====
On 16 August 2022, [[K.A.A. Gent|Gent]] announced that Hauge would join the [[Belgian First Division A]] club on a season-long loan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kaagent.be/nl/nieuws/16-08-2022/velkommen-jens-petter|title=Velkommen Jens Petter!|trans-title=Welcome Jens Petter!|language=nl|publisher=[[K.A.A. Gent|Gent]]|date=16 August 2022}}</ref>

===Return to Bodø/Glimt===
On 31 January 2024, Hauge returned to [[FK Bodø/Glimt|Bodø/Glimt]] on loan until the end of 2024, with an option to buy.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Bodø/Glimt]|url=https://www.glimt.no/nyheter/jens-petter-tilbake-i-gult--aldri-tatt-foten-av-gasspedalen|title=JENS PETTER TILBAKE I GULT: – ALDRI TATT FOTEN AV GASSPEDALEN|trans-title=JENS PETTER BACK IN YELLOW: - NEVER TOOK MY FOOT OFF THE GAS PEDAL|date=31 January 2024|access-date=31 January 2024|language=no}}</ref> On 16 January 2025, he joined the club on a permanent deal by signing a contract until 2028.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.glimt.no/nyheter/jens-petter-hauge-tilbake-i-glimt--her-kan-jeg-utvikle-meg-videre |title=Jens Petter Hauge tilbake i Glimt: – Her kan jeg utvikle meg videre |publisher=FK Bodø/Glimt |language=no |date=16 January 2025 }}</ref>

He scored his first [[UEFA Champions League]] goals by netting a brace in a 2–2 draw with [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] on 30 September 2025.<ref>{{cite web |last=Rose |first=Gary |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c8xr9489pret |title=Bodø / Glimt 2–2 Tottenham Hotspur |publisher=BBC Sport |date=30 September 2025 }}</ref> During the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|2025–26 Champions League knockout play-offs]], he scored in both legs and provided an assist in 5–2 victory on aggregate over [[Inter Milan]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/live-blogs/inter-vs-bodo-glimt-live-updates-champions-league-score-result/zKS2ahLeUiN1/lkrXFTOxjCKa/ |title=How Bodo/Glimt beat Inter again to secure stunning Champions League upset |publisher=The New York Times |date=25 February 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
He made his [[Norway national football team|national team]] debut on 11 October 2020 in a [[2020–21 UEFA Nations League B|Nations League]] game against [[Romania national football team|Romania]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[ESPN]]|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match?gameId=570739|title=Norway v Romania game report|date=11 October 2020|access-date=15 October 2020|archive-date=15 October 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201015151617/https://www.espn.com/soccer/match?gameId=570739|url-status=live}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Hauge has a younger brother, [[Runar Hauge|Runar]], who is also a professional footballer who plays for [[Hobro IK]]. The pair has played together for [[FK Bodø/Glimt|Bodø/Glimt]], the club where they both made their debuts.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nettavisen.no/sport/fotball/norge-talentets-uvanlige-problem-vi-ble-tatt-litt-pa-senga/s/12-95-3423483727|title=Norge-talentets uvanlige problem: - Vi ble tatt litt på senga|date=9 May 2018}}</ref>

